recipe.instructions:
For each 1 cup buttermilk called for in a recipe, use 1 cup plain yogurt or sour cream;

OR

1 tablespoon lemon juice or vinegar plus enough milk to make 1 cup;

OR

1 cup milk plus 1 3/4 tablespoons cream of tartar;

&lt;b&gt;Prepare the Meatballs&lt;/b&gt;
Combine the break crumbs and heavy cream in a small bowl, stirring with a fork until all the crumbs are moistened. Set aside.

Heat the oil in a small skillet over hedium heat. Add the onion and saute for about 5 minutes, until softened. Remove from the heat.

In a large bowl, combine the ground beef, veal, pork, onion, honey, and egg, and mix will with your hands. Season with salt and pepper to taste. Add the bread crumb-cream mixture and mix well. With wet hands (to keep the mixture from sticking), share the mixture into meatballs the size of a golf ball, placing them on a plate lightly moisented with water. You should have about 24 meatballs.

Melt the butter in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add the meatballs, in batches if necessary, and cook, turning freuently, for about 7 minutes, until browned on all sides and cooked through. Transfer the meatballs to a plate, and discard all but 1 tablesppoon of fat from the skillet.
&lt;b&gt;
Prepare the Sauce&lt;/b&gt;
Return the skillet to the heat, whisk in the stock, cream, preserves, and pickle juice, and bring to a simmer. Season to taste with salt and pepper. Add the meatballs to the sauce, reduce the heat to medium, and simmer for about 5 minutes, until the sauce thickens slightly and the meatballs are heated through.
